<subSubSection id="2F6C50CB93F80D32C7907678D987A580" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="D32193C1C683D26976C9A3D161674B31" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="794EC9C0A5840A2E35ECEE97DD01607B" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
3.5-4.2 mm long (mean = 3.73 mm; n = 5); 2.1-2.3
<normalizedToken id="C0DFD997ED0CAE725B3123E8AB7054E2" originalValue="Ã—">x</normalizedToken>
as long as wide. This species is distinguished by the presence of more than three spines on each elytral margin, declivital armature consists of two large spines closest to suture on declivital summit and many smaller, uniformly sized denticles on declivital margin.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
